(2, 'I never did anything by accident, nor did any of my inventions come by accident; they came by work', 'Thomas A. Edison'),
(3, 'I start where the last man left off', 'Thomas A. Edison'),
(4, 'The noblest pleasure is the joy of understanding', 'Leonardo da Vinci'),
(5, 'Logic will get you from A to B. Imagination will take you everywhere', 'Albert Einstein'),
(6, 'It is a miracle that curiosity survives formal education', 'Albert Einstein'),
(7, 'Difficulties mastered are opportunities won', 'Winston Churchill'),
(8, 'If you can dream it, you can do it', 'Walt Disney'),
(9, 'Your brain is much better than you think; just use it', 'Leonardo Da Vinci'),
(10, 'Before you can do something that you’ve never done, you have to be able to imagine it is possibl', 'Jean Bolen'),
(12, 'I am always doing that which I can not do, in order that I may learn how to do it', 'Pablo Picasso'),
(13, 'I hear and forget. I see and remember. I do and understand', 'Confucious'),
